[0.061, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf you hit a\u001b[16Gcompiler bug, mini\u001b[35Gize it first: bisect to the smallest source that still triggers it, and find the \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bclosest variant that *does* compile, so the trigger is pinned down precisely (not just \"my big program failed\"). Then\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bwrite it t\u001b[14G a `BUG-<slug>.md` file in the project root with a\u001b[65Gone-l\u001b[71Gne title, the\u001b[85G`pr\u001b[89Gmise version` output, your \u001b[39m    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mplatform, the minimal repro (smallest `.pr` source plus the exact `promise build` command), the verbatim error \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Boutput, the expected behavior, a shor\u001b[42Gtable of wha\u001b[56Gd\u001b[58Ges and doesn't trigger i\u001b[83G, your\u001b[90Gbest guess at the cause, and \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe workaround you use\u001b[26G in the real code. Verify the re\u001b[59Gro actually fail\u001b[76G and the\u001b[85G\"compiles fine\" controls actually \u001b[39m \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mcompile before writing the\u001b[30G down —\u001b[38Gdon't go from mem\u001b[56Gry.\u001b[39m                                            "]
[0.000, "o", "             \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                                                                               \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIf the task\u001b[15Gneeds somet\u001b[27Ging Promi\u001b[37Ge doesn't have ye\u001b[56G— a standard-libra\u001b[75Gy module that isn'\u001b[95Gth\u001b[98Gre, or a missing\u001b[115G\u001b[39m    \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mlanguage feature —\u001b[22Gdon't fake it silently. Bu\u001b[49Gld\u001b[56Gclosest clean thing you can,\u001b[85Gor, if it's a hard bl\u001b[107Gcker, stop \u001b[39m \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mand say\u001b[11Gwhy. Either way r\u001b[29Gcord the\u001b[38Ggap in a\u001b[47G`FEATURE-<slug>.md` file in the project root: a one-line title, the \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B`promise version` output, what you needed and why the task called for it, what's missing (e.g. no standard module for\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BX,\u001b[6Gno languag\u001b[17G supp\u001b[23Grt for Y), whether it block\u001b[51Gd you outright or just force\u001b[80G a workarou\u001b[92Gd,\u001b[98G workaround you used,\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band — if\u001b[12Gyou can\u001b[22Ga **sketch\u001b[33Gof\u001b[36Gthe API or syntax**\u001b[56Gthat would have made it\u001b[81G"]
