[0.019, "o", "\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[6BOwnership semantics differ from the guide's description. Let me probe the actual rule for passing a \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mstring\u001b[39m local to a\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bplain-\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mstring\u001b[39m param.\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;153;153;153mRan \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BContrary to the guide, a plain \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mstring\u001b[39m param \u001b[1mmoves\u001b[22m the argument. I need \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m&\u001b[39m to borrow. Let me confirm the borrow syntax.\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;2;153;153;153mRan \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe guide is wrong: a plain \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mstring\u001b[39m param \u001b[1mmoves\u001b[22m the arg at the call site but is treated as a non-movable borrow inside\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe callee. The real borrow form is \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mstring& s\u001b[39m. Let me verify a couple of consequences (borrowing a temporary/literal,\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Band re-use after a borrow) before rewriting with consistent borrow discipline.\u001b[K\r\u001b[41C\u001b[12B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m · esc to interrupt\u001b[39m\u001b[30;1H\u001b["]
